			.dmpage-main
				.dmpage-detail
					.dmpage-text
						p In 2022, the Board of Directors approved the climate section of the Development Strategy. The long-term goal setting is based on the vector of achieving carbon neutrality by 2050 in terms of controlled greenhouse gas emissions (Scope 1 and 2, taking into account compensating measures and the development of low-carbon technologies). Mid-term targets propose reducing in carbon intensity by 14% by 2025 and 30% by 2030 compared to the baseline year 2021.

						h3 Specific greenhouse gas emissions (Scope 1 and 2)

						img(src="https://www.tatneft.ru/uploads/publications/dmpages/prilozheniya/processed_new_pictures/from_en/image88.jpg", alt="")

						
					.dmpage-quote
						p Since 2020, the Company has integrated greenhouse gas emission reduction indicators into its management KPIs.
						p The KPI system for SDG 13 encompasses a range of indicators crucial to accomplishing the goals, in particular:
						p 1. Not exceeding the target greenhouse gas emissions (Scope 1+2) for the TATNEFT Group is integrated into the KPI of the Deputy General Director in charge of environmental and climate issues in the Company.  This metric is then broken down to the heads of business streams and enterprises; each of whom is responsible for ensuring that emissions within their functional scope of activity do not exceed the specified target.
						p 2. The introduction of compulsory reporting on greenhouse gas emissions prompted the inclusion of KPIs regarding the timing and quality of greenhouse gas emissions reporting.
						p 3. The project manager's key performance indicators (KPIs) measure the delivery of key projects that contribute to the reduction of greenhouse gas emissions. 


					.dmpage-text
						p Main levers of decarbonization:

						ul
							li technological solutions to reduce emissions - reducing direct greenhouse gas emissions, reducing methane emissions, improving energy efficiency, increasing the level of utilization of associated petroleum gas
							li carbon capture, utilization and storage
							li development of renewable energy
							li biological capture of distributed CO2 emissions
							li formation of an ecological worldview and involvement of the population in the implementation of SDGs


						h2 IMPLEMENTATION OF THE SDG 13 PROGRAM AND DECARBONIZATION OF THE COMPANY ARE ACCOMPLISHED THROUGH A SET OF SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT GOALS. 
						img(src="https://www.tatneft.ru/uploads/publications/dmpages/prilozheniya/processed_new_pictures/from_en/image86.jpg", alt="")

						h3 CARBON FOOTPRINT REDUCTION PROJECTS AND PROGRESS
						p In order to achieve SDG 13 indicators, the Company has formed a portfolio of projects aimed at reducing the carbon footprint. The projects are included in the Climate Action Program. In 2022, the potential of the Greenhouse Gas Emissions Reduction Program has been increased from 1.9 million tonnes of CO2-eq. to 2.2 million tonnes of CO2-eq. (16%). The environmental effect of the Program implementation in 2022 amounted to 0.7 million tonnes of CO2-eq. 
						p The cost of implementing measures in 2022 is RUB 2.4 billion. The achieved effect for 2021-2022 amounted to 0.944 million tonnes of CO2-eq*. Targets for greenhouse gas emissions have been met in all business areas of the TATNEFT Group.
					.dmpage-text.dmpage-text--small
						p * The environmental effect of implementing by the Greenhouse Gas Emissions Reduction Program is figured out by comparing the baseline (which is the calculation of greenhouse gas emissions without taking any measures) with actual greenhouse gas emissions taking into account changes in the level of production activities. The calculation includes the greenhouse gas emissions Scope 1, 2, and 3.
					.dmpage-text
						p The calculation includes the greenhouse gas emissions Scope 1, 2, and 3.





					.dmpage-accordions-wrap
						.dmpage-accordions
							.dmpage-accordion
								.dmpage-accordion-head
									.dmpage-accordion-head__text Achievement of Sustainable Development Goals

