					.dmpage-text
						h2 PROJECTS TO REDUCE DIRECT AND INDIRECT GREENHOUSE GAS EMISSIONS  
						ul
							li Reduction of flare burning due to changes in the technological regime of separation at the Company's facilities, expansion of the gas collection system, increase in the level of utilization of waste gases at JSC TANECO allowed reducing emissions of more than 400 thousand tonnes of CO2-eq. 
							li The implementation of the X-Plate technology at LLC Nizhnekamsk CHP allowed reducing 15.9 thousand tonnes of CO2-eq.
							li The use of renewable energy sources has reduced greenhouse gas emissions by 2.4 thousand tonnes of CO2-eq. 
							li A number of projects and scientific research in the field of CCUS (Carbon Capture Utilization and Storage) have been implemented, the potential for capture amounted to 6.0 million tonnes of CO2. The R&D investment portfolio for the capture project is RUB 127.8 million.
							li Development of a system for monitoring methane emissions through the use of unmanned aerial vehicles that allow timely obtaining reliable data on technological malfunctions at facilities.

						h2 PROJECTS FOR THE IMPLEMENTATION OF COMPENSATION MEASURES  
						ul
							li Implementation of the program for planting and restoration of forests. In 2022, about 2.2 million trees were planted on an area of 1 325 hectares. Over 10 years of the program implementation, more than 20.5 million trees have been planted.

						h2 PROJECTS TO IMPROVE THE SYSTEM OF ACCOUNTING FOR GREENHOUSE GAS EMISSIONS 
						ul
							li Scope 3 perimeter of accounting for indirect greenhouse gas emissions has been increased: greenhouse gas emissions from employee air travel have been included. 
							li The process of calculating greenhouse gas emissions for the TATNEFT Group has been automated, software has been created that unites the Group's enterprises and ensures the integration of software with fuel and energy consumption accounting systems. 
							li In order to enhance the climate awareness and competence of the company's employees and to foster an environmentally oriented attitude, training courses have been developed: Simulation of work in the module "Greenhouse gases", "Climate agenda, sustainable development goals and the Company's position in the field of climate".